  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (stale requirement binding)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Model baseline updated to 2025-Q3 platform incorporating revised impeller geometry tolerances per internal design change notice DCN-2025-047; requirement binding retained against ASME V&V 40-2018 without noting the 2022 addendum (Addendum A) that revised Section 5 credibility factor gradation tables for hemolysis-relevant QoIs.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vv40-2018-mrl2-hemolysis",
