      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison between simulation outputs and experimental measurements performed using appropriate metrics. Required level 2 per MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "RHI predictions compared against experimental measurements at all 5 operating points. Mean absolute error 8.3%; maximum point error 14.1% at highest flow-speed combination. Comparison performed using normalized index of agreement. All predictions fall within experimental uncertainty bounds at 95% confidence. Output comparison level 2 achieved per ASME V&V 40-2018."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation are relevant to and representative of the COU decision QoIs. Required level 2 per MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Relative hemolysis index (RHI) is the primary regulatory QoI for CPB hemolysis assessment per FDA guidance. Shear stress scalar field and exposure time are intermediate QoIs directly linked to RHI via Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model. QoI relevance to COU decision (worst-case operating condition identification) is direct. Level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities address the physics, geometry, and operating conditions relevant to the COU with documented similarity assessment. Required level 2 per MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which shares impeller topology and operating regime with the subject CPB device. Geometric similarity index 0.87 (dimensionless impeller diameter ratio, clearance ratio). Reynolds number and flow coefficient overlap between validation and COU operating points documented in similarity assessment SA-2025-001. Level 2 achieved."
    },
